<%
  set_seo_meta(
    title: "Return Policy - BizBlasts",
    description: "BizBlasts return and refund policy: how refunds work for BizBlasts subscriptions and how independent businesses handle their own customer refunds.",
    canonical: "https://www.bizblasts.com/returnpolicy"
  )

  effective_date = "June 1, 2026"
  support_email  = ENV.fetch('SUPPORT_EMAIL', 'bizblaststeam@gmail.com')
%>

<%= render layout: 'shared/legal_page',
           locals: {
             eyebrow: 'Return Policy',
             title: 'Return and Refund Policy',
             summary: "How refunds and returns work for the BizBlasts platform, and how each independent business that uses BizBlasts sets its own customer-facing return policy.",
             effective_date: effective_date,
             contact_email: support_email
           } do %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '1. BizBlasts Subscription Fees' } do %>
    <p>
      BizBlasts subscription fees and one-time service fees are non-refundable except as expressly stated
      below or as required by applicable law. Cancelling a subscription stops future renewals; it does not,
      by itself, generate a refund for the current billing period.
    </p>
    <p>
      We may offer specific promotional refund terms from time to time (for example, a money-back window for
      a new plan). Any such offer is limited to its stated terms and may be denied for abuse, fraud, repeated
      refund requests, or material violation of our
      <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', '/terms', class: 'text-primary hover:underline' %>.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '2. Cancellations and Downgrades' } do %>
    <p>
      You can cancel your BizBlasts subscription at any time from your dashboard or by contacting support.
      Cancellation takes effect at the end of your current billing period, and you retain access until then.
      When you downgrade to a lower tier, premium features (such as custom-domain hosting) may stop working
      at the start of the next billing period.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '3. Goods and Services Sold by Independent Businesses' } do %>
    <p>
      Many transactions on BizBlasts are between an end customer and an independent business that uses our
      platform. For those transactions:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>The transaction is between the customer and the underlying business, not BizBlasts.</li>
      <li>Each business sets its own return, refund, exchange, cancellation, no-show, and deposit policies.</li>
      <li>Each business is responsible for honoring those policies, communicating them to its customers, and complying with any applicable consumer-protection laws.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Customers should look for return and cancellation terms on the product or service page, in the cart, or
      in published policy pages on the business&rsquo;s site, and should contact the business directly to
      request a return or refund.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '4. Payment Disputes and Chargebacks' } do %>
    <p>
      Payments are processed by our payment provider (currently Stripe). When a customer disputes a charge,
      the payment provider&rsquo;s dispute process applies. The business that received the payment is
      responsible for responding to the dispute and providing evidence; BizBlasts is not a party to the
      underlying transaction. BizBlasts platform fees may not be refundable on disputed transactions.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '5. Refund Tools for Businesses' } do %>
    <p>
      The BizBlasts dashboard provides tools to help businesses issue refunds for orders, bookings, deposits,
      and tips processed through the platform. Use of those tools is governed by the business&rsquo;s own
      policies and by the payment provider&rsquo;s rules.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '6. Changes' } do %>
    <p>
      We may update this Return Policy from time to time by posting a revised version on the site and
      updating the effective date above.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '7. Contact' } do %>
    <p>
      Questions about BizBlasts subscription refunds or this Return Policy may be sent to
      <%= mail_to support_email, support_email, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>.
      For refunds or returns on goods or services purchased from a business through their BizBlasts site,
      please contact that business directly.
    </p>
  <% end %>

<% end %>
